{"title": "Unsanitized user input in code generation", "summary": "  Applications should not look up or manipulate code using user-supplied data. ", "description": "\n\nApplications should not look up or manipulate code using user-supplied data.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid using user input when using reflection:\n\n```ruby\nmethod(params[:method])\n```\n\n\u2705 Use user input indirectly when using reflection:\n\n```ruby\nmethod_name =\n  case params[:action]\n  when \"option1\"\n    \"method1\"\n  when \"option2\"\n    \"method2\"\n  end\n\nmethod(method_name)\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-94"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/ruby_lang_reflection_using_user_input", "https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/Code_Injection"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}